                    </div>
                    <span>It seems that the author has a fear of not being able to deliver a satisfying content. Thus he comes arond many issues by writing to meny humorous bits that (in the long run) tends to get in the way of the actual information. -I prefer a natural mixture of both information and humour.<br>-But, if the reader is able to look through (or like) the author's personal jitter, it can be a quite an informative book.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Good intro</div>
                    <div>
